<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='308331' id='t-308331'>At the time I was just beginning to emerge</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='311580' id='t-311580'>from this eight-year personal identity crisis zigzag</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='315497' id='t-315497'>that saw me go from being a boy</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='317330' id='t-317330'>to being this awkward girl that looked like a boy in girl's clothes</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='320552' id='t-320552'>to the opposite extreme of this super skimpy,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='323342' id='t-323342'>over-compensating, boy-chasing girly-girl</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='326008' id='t-326008'>to finally just a hesitant exploration of what I actually was,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='329976' id='t-329976'>a tomboyish girl</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='332383' id='t-332383'>who liked both boys and girls depending on the person.</span>
</span>
