 7:42
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='451034' id='t-451034'>For me, photography is not just about exposing film,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='454431' id='t-454431'>it's about exposing the viewer</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='456384' id='t-456384'>to something new, a place they haven't gone before,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='458485' id='t-458485'>but most importantly, to people that they might be afraid of.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='461800' id='t-461800'>Life magazine introduced generations of people</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='463644' id='t-463644'>to distant, far-off cultures they never knew existed through pictures.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='467718' id='t-467718'>So I decided to make a series of very simple portraits,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='473951' id='t-473951'>mugshots if you will.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='475701' id='t-475701'>And I basically decided to photograph anyone in this country</span>
